<h3>Help: Pages</h3>

<p>The <b>Pages</b> section of the CMS is where you can edit the non-repetitive content on your site. This includes things like headers, page body text and contact details. For repetitive content such as products, galleries or news see <b>Data</b>.</p>

<p>To edit page content firsly go to the <b>Pages</b> section of the CMS. You'll now see down the left under <b>All Pages</b> a full list of the pages that have editable content. Click on of these to starte editing. Once you've finished editing make sure you click the <b>Update</b> button at the bottom of the page to save your information.</p>